# To-Do List Application

A simple and dynamic to-do list application built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
This project allows users to manage their daily tasks efficiently by adding, completing, and deleting tasks. 
It features a user-friendly interface with real-time updates and smooth animations for task management.

# Features

-> User-Friendly Interface: Simple and clean design, making it easy to add, manage, and filter tasks.
-> Task Management: Users can add tasks with titles and descriptions, mark tasks as complete, and delete tasks permanently.
-> Task Filters: Filter tasks by their status (pending, completed, or deleted).
-> Local Storage: Tasks are saved in the browser's local storage, ensuring that user data is not lost even after refreshing the page.
-> Theme Toggle: Option to switch between light and dark themes for a personalized experience.
-> Real-Time Display: Tasks are updated instantly on the screen as users interact with the interface.

# Technologies Used

HTML: Structure of the to-do list.
CSS: Handles Styling.
JavaScript: Handles task management, filtering, local storage, and theme toggling.

# Functionalities

Add Task: Users can add new tasks by entering a title and description.
Mark as Complete: Tasks can be marked as complete, which moves them to the completed section with an animation.
Delete Task: Users can delete tasks, either moving them to a deleted section or permanently removing them.
Filter Tasks: Filter tasks based on their status (pending, completed, or deleted) using a dropdown menu.
Theme Toggle: Switch between light and dark themes, with the theme choice saved locally.
Local Storage: Tasks are stored in local storage, ensuring persistence even after the page is refreshed.

How It Works
Event Listeners: JavaScript event listeners like "click" and "change" are used to handle user inputs and trigger actions such as adding, completing, or deleting tasks.
Animations: Task transitions like completing or deleting are animated using CSS, providing a smooth user experience.
Task Persistence: The application uses local storage to persist tasks, ensuring that task data is retained between sessions.
Theme Toggle: The theme toggle button allows switching between light and dark modes, with the preference stored locally.
